<br>
Camp a zone expect people to train ya.  That goes for any zone in the game.  Most don't mean to but one lil thing like an invis drop in CT and there ya go.  Theres also one mob in the courtyard that sees invis in CT.<br>
<br>
If u still plan to camp a zone in and a large crowd is going thru,  the mobs you are camping are probably gonna get shredded fast when they plow through.  Like you said there was like 40 of em.<br>
<br>
I don't know what was said in /ooc i'm sure it fueled tempers.  None the less, next time you go to CT, invis and move in to a safer spot if you want to avoid unwanted trains.  Doesn't matter if its a raid party or a small group... one invis drop and someone is gonna bring u adds while they run for the zone.  This reminds me of people camping KC zone out and freaking when they get trained or one of their front 2 mobs get killed by someone who agroed them when they repopped on em.<br>
<br>
Best bet for when you have a conflict with a guild like this is send a /tell to a member and ask who the raid leader is and send them a tell.  If you take it to /ooc you have to deal with players like Gaeele who will try ti kill u irl )  <br>
<br>
CC has good people who run their raids.  Send them a tell next time and things will go much smoother.  <br>
<br>
My thoughts.  Open for debate i dont give a fuck.<br>
<br>
Peace<br>
